  "title": "Hip Ligaments",
  "body_html": "The ligamentum teres transmits the foveal artery, it has little significance as a ligament unless the hip is dislocated when it is then stretched.<br /><br />The transverse ligament is in fact part of the acetabular labrum.<br /><br />There are three extracapsular ligaments of the hip:-<br /><br /><b>Iliofemoral</b> It originates from the ilium, immediately inferior to the anterior inferior iliac spine.The ligament attaches to the intertrochanteric line in two places, giving the ligament a Y shaped appearance. It prevents hyperextension of the hip joint.<br /><br /><b>Ischiofemoral</b> It originates from the ischium of the pelvis and attaches to the greater trochanter of the femur.  It prevents excessive extension of the femur at the hip joint. <br /><br /><b>Pubofemoral</b> It attaches at the pelvis to the iliopubic eminance and obturator membrane, and then blends with the articular capsule. It prevents excessive abduction and extension.<br /><br /><i>illustrating the ligaments of the hip</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb225b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb225.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hip'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb225b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb226b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb226.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hip'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb226b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb227b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb227.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/hip'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb227b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">3</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Lower limb anatomy</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\nThe ligamentum teres transmits the foveal artery, it has little significance as a ligament unless the hip is dislocated when it is then stretched.<br /><br />The transverse ligament is in fact part of the acetabular labrum.<br /><br />There are three extracapsular ligaments of the hip:-<br /><br /><b>Iliofemoral</b> It originates from the ilium, immediately inferior to the anterior inferior iliac spine.The ligament attaches to the intertrochanteric line in two places, giving the ligament a Y shaped appearance. It prevents hyperextension of the hip joint.<br /><br /><b>Ischiofemoral</b> It originates from the ischium of the pelvis and attaches to the greater trochanter of the femur.  It prevents excessive extension of the femur at the hip joint. <br /><br /><b>Pubofemoral</b> It attaches at the pelvis to the iliopubic eminance and obturator membrane, and then blends with the articular capsule. It prevents excessive abduction and extension.<br /><br /><i>illustrating the ligaments of the hip</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb225b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb225.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hip'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb225b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb226b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb226.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hip'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'